  "chapter": {
    "number": 8,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Christ’s Eternal Priesthood"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "The point of what we are saying is this: We do have such a high priest, who sat down at the right hand of the throne of the Majesty in heaven,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "and who ministers in the sanctuary and true tabernacle set up by the Lord, not by man."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "And since every high priest is appointed to offer both gifts and sacrifices, it was necessary for this One also to have something to offer."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "Now if He were on earth, He would not be a priest, since there are already priests who offer gifts according to the law."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "The place where they serve is a copy and shadow of what is in heaven. This is why Moses was warned when he was about to build the tabernacle: “See to it that you make everything according to the pattern shown you on the mountain.”",
          {
            "noteId": 2396
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The New Covenant"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "Now, however, Jesus has received a much more excellent ministry, just as the covenant He mediates is better and is founded on better promises."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "For if that first covenant had been without fault, no place would have been sought for a second."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "But God found fault with the people and said:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Behold, the days are coming, declares the Lord,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when I will make a new covenant",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "with the house of Israel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and with the house of Judah.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It will not be like the covenant",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I made with their fathers",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "when I took them by the hand",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to lead them out of the land of Egypt,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because they did not abide by My covenant,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I disregarded them,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the Lord."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For this is the covenant I will make",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with the house of Israel",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "after those days,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the Lord.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will put My laws in their minds",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and inscribe them on their hearts.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "And I will be their God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they will be My people.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "No longer will each one teach his neighbor or his brother,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "saying, ‘Know the Lord,’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because they will all know Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the least of them to the greatest.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I will forgive their iniquities",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and will remember their sins no more.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2397
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "By speaking of a new covenant,",
          {
            "noteId": 2398
          },
          "He has made the first one obsolete; and what is obsolete and aging will soon disappear."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 2396,
